qas.question: What is the term for a relationship where one organism provides a dwelling for the other?
What type of relationship is it when arachnids attach webs to dead plants?
In what type of relationship does an organism travel by means of another?
Where do the spiders build their webs on the hermit crabs?
What is the term for a relationship where one organism refuses to provide a dwelling for the other?
What occurs when the spider utilizes phoresy with the hermit crab?

plausible_answers.text: one organism using something another created

qas.question: What can commensal relationships between plants and hermit crabs be considered?
When one organism gives away something another created what is it called?

context: <b7_0>Commensal relationships<b7_0/> may involve one organism using another for transportation (<a2_0>phoresy<a2_0/>) or for housing (<a0_0><b4_0>inquilinism<b4_0/><a0_0/>), or it may also involve <b6_0>one organism using something another created<b6_0/>, after its death (<a1_0><b5_0>metabiosis<b5_0/><a1_0/>). Examples of metabiosis are hermit crabs using <b3_0>gastropod shells<b3_0/> to protect their bodies and spiders building their webs on plants.
